claims:
11. A computer-usable storage medium having instructions embodied therein that when executed cause a plurality of computing systems to perform a method for distributing a graph storage system in a fault tolerant manner, said method comprising:
storing said graph storage system on a plurality of computing systems within said plurality of computing systems, wherein said graph storage system comprises graph objects;
providing a global address space for distributed graph storage;
managing said global address space with graph allocators, wherein a graph allocator of said graph allocators allocates space from a block of said distributed global memory assigned for use by said graph allocator in order to store a plurality of graphs;
performing distributed graph traversals on said graph storage system; and
employing a fault toleration structure for concurrency-safe access to said graph objects stored in said plurality of computing systems.
